ENTRY            A0607   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0607001   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 15         36
TITLE      Interaction of 238U with 300- and 11.5-GeV protons:
           Cross sections and recoil properties in the
           A ~ 130 mass region
AUTHOR     (Y.W.Yu,N.T.Porile)
INSTITUTE  (1USAPUR)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,10,167,1974)
FACILITY   (SYNCY,1USAANL) The ZGS at Argonne National Laboratory.
METHOD     (STTA,INTB,EXTB,CHSEP)
SAMPLE     The target stacks consisted of 20 um depleted uranium
           foil surrounded by three layers of 20 um high-purity
            (99.999%) aluminium. The innermost foils served as
           recoil catchers, the middle foils as beam monitors,
           and the outer ones as guard foils. In the case of the
           300-GeV bombardments, the target stacks were sealed
           in evacuated plastic bags in order to prevent the air
           layer between target and catcher foils.
ADD-RES    (COMP) Thick-target recoil properties have been
           determined.
DETECTOR   (GELI) A calibrated 70 cm3 Ge(LI) detector or thin
           Ge(LI) X-ray detector.
CORRECTION The listed values have been corrected for secondary
           effects on both the uranium and monitor reactions.
MONITOR    ((MONIT)13-AL-27(P,N+3P)11-NA-24,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (B0022001,J.Cumming,J,ARN,13,261,1963)
ERR-ANALYS The actual uncertainties in the cross sections
           include in addition to the listed standard deviations
           the errors in branching ratios, detector efficiencies,
           and cross sections of the monitor reactions.
           (ERR-S) The experimental standard deviations are based
           on the indicated number of replicate determination.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Y.W.Yu+,J,PR/C,10,167,1974) Table II
HISTORY    (19981118C)
           (19990210U) Last checking has been done.
           (19990318A) DATE is corrected
           (20120120A) NDS(VZ): REL-REF: ND/B->NDS in 002-004,008
           (20260204A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              36
